This paper is primarily focused on congestion control protocols in computer networks, which falls under the category of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also uses tools from control theory and bifurcation theory to analyze the stability and behavior of the RCP system, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and optimization of the RCP protocol, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
